keywords trip
---
Syntax: trip <target>

Attempts to sweep an opponent's legs out from under them, knocking them to
the ground. A tripped target is left in a vulnerable position for follow-up
attacks. Success is based on your learned proficiency in the trip skill.

The target must already be engaged in combat (fighting someone) for trip
to work. Trip also costs energy via the energy system.

A successful trip initiates combat between you and the target if you were
not already fighting. The knockdown effect reduces the target's ability to
fight back temporarily.

Requirements:
  - Target must be fighting someone (already in combat).
  - Must have energy available.
  - Must have the skill learned.

See also: shelp trip bash dirt stun
